					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Putative reforms of the Roman military in 107 BC</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:RRC_326.1_Gaius_Fundanius_depicting_Gaius_Marius_triumphator.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/RRC_326.1_Gaius_Fundanius_depicting_Gaius_Marius_triumphator.png/220px-RRC_326.1_Gaius_Fundanius_depicting_Gaius_Marius_triumphator.png" decoding="async" width="220" height="220" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/RRC_326.1_Gaius_Fundanius_depicting_Gaius_Marius_triumphator.png/330px-RRC_326.1_Gaius_Fundanius_depicting_Gaius_Marius_triumphator.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/RRC_326.1_Gaius_Fundanius_depicting_Gaius_Marius_triumphator.png/440px-RRC_326.1_Gaius_Fundanius_depicting_Gaius_Marius_triumphator.png 2x" data-file-width="2194" data-file-height="2194" /></a><figcaption><a href="/wiki/Gaius_Marius" title="Gaius Marius">Gaius Marius</a>, depicted as a <a href="/wiki/Roman_triumph" title="Roman triumph">triumphator</a> in a coin minted by Gaius Fundanius in 101&#160;BC. He triumphed due to his victory in the <a href="/wiki/Cimbric_War" class="mw-redirect" title="Cimbric War">Cimbric War</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></figcaption></figure>
