<li id="cite_note-90"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-90">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">No trace, for example, of the Marian reforms is found at <cite id="CITEREFSmith1848" class="citation encyclopaedia cs1">Smith, William, ed. (1848). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0104%3Aentry%3Dmarius-bio-1">"Marius"</a>. <i>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology</i>. London: John Murray &#8211; via Perseus.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Marius&amp;rft.btitle=Dictionary+of+Greek+and+Roman+Biography+and+Mythology&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=John+Murray&amp;rft.date=1848&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.perseus.tufts.edu%2Fhopper%2Ftext%3Fdoc%3DPerseus%253Atext%253A1999.04.0104%253Aentry%253Dmarius-bio-1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMarian+reforms" class="Z3988"></span></span>
