<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Ancient">Ancient</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Marian_reforms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Ancient"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<div class="refbegin refbegin-columns references-column-width" style="column-width: 30em">
<ul><li><cite id="CITEREFPlut._Mar." class="citation book cs1">Plutarch (1920) [2nd century AD]. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Marius*.html">"Life of Marius"</a>. <i>Parallel Lives</i>. Loeb Classical Library. Vol.&#160;9. Translated by Perrin, Bernadotte. William Heinemann. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/40115288">40115288</a> &#8211; via LacusCurtius.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Life+of+Marius&amp;rft.btitle=Parallel+Lives&amp;rft.series=Loeb+Classical+Library&amp;rft.pub=William+Heinemann&amp;rft.date=1920&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F40115288&amp;rft.au=Plutarch&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fpenelope.uchicago.edu%2FThayer%2FE%2FRoman%2FTexts%2FPlutarch%2FLives%2FMarius%2A.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMarian+reforms" class="Z3988"></span></li>
